# SafeLife is a static Next.js app (output: "export") — no server-side env vars are read at runtime.
#
# The Claude-backed Ask + Scam features are opt-in and BYOK ("bring your own key"):
# users paste an Anthropic API key in the in-app Settings screen. It's stored only
# in the browser's localStorage under the key `safelife:anthropic-key` and is sent
# only to api.anthropic.com.
#
# There is deliberately no ANTHROPIC_API_KEY variable here — nothing on the server
# uses one. Do not commit a key into this file or into localStorage backups.

# Landing-page waitlist form (Formspree). Create a free form at https://formspree.io,
# copy the form ID from the URL (e.g. "abcdwxyz"), and set it here or in the Vercel
# dashboard (Settings → Environment Variables). Without this, the form still submits
# in "demo mode" and logs to the browser console instead of collecting signups.
NEXT_PUBLIC_FORMSPREE_ID=
